skinparam backgroundColor #1a1a2e
skinparam defaultFontColor #ffffff
skinparam defaultFontName "Segoe UI"
skinparam rectangle {
    BackgroundColor #0f3460
    BorderColor #58a6ff
    FontColor #ffffff
    RoundCorner 8
}
skinparam arrow {
    Color #58a6ff
}
skinparam note {
    BackgroundColor #16213e
    BorderColor #3fb950
    FontColor #ffffff
}

title Complexity Hierarchy: From Constant to Factorial

rectangle "**O(1)**\nConstant" as O1 #1a472a {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Array index access
        • Hash table lookup
        • Stack push/pop
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: 1
        n=10⁶: 1
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(log n)**\nLogarithmic" as Olog #1a472a {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Binary search
        • Balanced BST lookup
        • Heap operations
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: ~3
        n=10⁶: ~20
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(n)**\nLinear" as On #1a472a {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Linear search
        • Array traversal
        • Finding max/min
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: 10
        n=10⁶: 10⁶
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(n log n)**\nLinearithmic" as Onlogn #3d5a4a {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Merge sort
        • Heapsort
        • FFT
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: ~33
        n=10⁶: ~2×10⁷
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(n²)**\nQuadratic" as On2 #5a3d3d {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Bubble sort
        • Selection sort
        • Nested loops
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: 100
        n=10⁶: 10¹²
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(n³)**\nCubic" as On3 #6b3d3d {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Matrix multiplication (naïve)
        • Floyd-Warshall
        • 3D simulations
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: 1,000
        n=10⁶: 10¹⁸
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(2ⁿ)**\nExponential" as O2n #7a2d2d {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Subset enumeration
        • Fibonacci (naïve)
        • Tower of Hanoi
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: ~1,000
        n=30: ~10⁹
    end note
}

rectangle "**O(n!)**\nFactorial" as Ofact #8b1d1d {
    note right
        **Examples:**
        • Permutation generation
        • Brute-force TSP
        • Determinant (Leibniz)
        
        **Growth:**
        n=10: ~3.6×10⁶
        n=20: ~2.4×10¹⁸
    end note
}

O1 -down-> Olog : slower
Olog -down-> On : slower
On -down-> Onlogn : slower
Onlogn -down-> On2 : slower
On2 -down-> On3 : slower
On3 -down-> O2n : slower
O2n -down-> Ofact : slower

note bottom of Ofact
    **Practical Limits (at 10⁹ ops/sec):**
    • O(n²) with n=10⁶: ~11.5 days
    • O(2ⁿ) with n=50: ~35 years
    • O(n!) with n=20: ~77 years
end note

@enduml
